from datetime import datetime
from pyspark.sql.functions import udf
from pyspark.sql.types import *
from __future__ import unicode_literals
#datetime.strptime('2017-11-05 14:32:21', '%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S').weekday()

def findday(valu):
    line = datetime.strptime(valu, '%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S').strftime('%d')
    return str(line)

udf_day = udf(findday, StringType())

train_df = train_df.withColumn("date_day",udf_day("click_time"))

def findhour(valu):
    line = datetime.strptime(valu, '%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S').hour
    return str(line)

udf_hour = udf(findhour, StringType())

train_df = train_df.withColumn("date_hour",udf_hour("click_time"))

%spark2.pyspark
train_df.registerTempTable('train_df_table')

%spark2.pyspark
train_df = train_df.drop('click_time')

# Index labels, adding metadata to the label column.
from pyspark.ml.linalg import Vectors
from pyspark.ml.feature import VectorAssembler

vect_train = VectorAssembler(inputCols=["app", "device", "os", "channel", "date_weekday", "date_hour"],outputCol="features").transform(train_df_vec)

vect_train.select("features","is_attributed")

%spark2.pyspark
#traindata.columns[7:]
# Fit on whole dataset to include all labels in index.
labelIndexer = StringIndexer(inputCol="is_attributed", outputCol="indexedLabel").fit(vect_train)

%spark2.pyspark
# Automatically identify categorical features, and index them.
# Set maxCategories so features with > 4 distinct values are treated as continuous. (, maxCategories=4)
featureIndexer = VectorIndexer(inputCol='features', outputCol="indexedFeatures").fit(vect_train)

# Split the data into training and test sets (30% held out for testing)
(trainingData, testData) = vect_train.randomSplit([0.9, 0.1])

%spark2.pyspark
# Train a Random Forest model.
#trainingData.select("features","is_attributed").take(5)
rf = RandomForestClassifier(labelCol="is_attributed", featuresCol="features", numTrees=10)

%spark2.pyspark
# Chain RF in a Pipeline
pipeline = Pipeline(stages=[rf])

%spark2.pyspark
# Train model.
model = pipeline.fit(trainingData)

%spark2.pyspark

from pyspark.sql.functions import lit
testData.withColumn('is_attributed', lit(None).cast(StringType()))

%spark2.pyspark

predictions = model.transform(testData)
